data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-form-a-business-288x288-20200728.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose a business entity."></div></div><p>For a cleaning business, we recommend opening a sole proprietorship or a Limited Liability Company (LLC). With a sole proprietorship, you have complete managerial control and it's easy to setup. An LLC takes advantage of the benefits of both a corporation and a partnership.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-cleaning-business-section6-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
