ents made by your staff, as you would need to move heavy equipment in many cases.<\/p>\n<p>If you are starting a residential cleaning business without a crew, you can use your private motor vehicle until you expand. Bear in mind that some states require you to get a commercial license plate before you are allowed to use your private vehicle for business purposes.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-cleaning-business#how-to-start-a-cleaning-business-section9-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-try-not-to-overspend-288x288-20200729.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Choose a vehicle with good storage space.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>The best vehicle for your cleaning business is a van, truck, station wagon, or SUV. Your cleaning business needs a heavy-duty vehicle\u2014and eventually more than one\u2014to store and transport your staff and equipment. The vehicle you need depends on the type and the size of your equipment.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-cleaning-business#how-to-start-a-cleaning-business-section9-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-look-for-a-vehicle-that-offers-loads-of-storage-288x288-20200729.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>You can use your vehicle as an advertising tool for your cleaning business. You can put advertising on your vehicle, which enables you to promote your cleaning business as you go.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"10","name":"<p>Recruit and train staff.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Determine your ideal candidate.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Your cleaning business is only as good as its employees. Therefore, your crew needs to be efficient, customer-focused, and able to deal with unique on-the-job challenges. To attract and recruit top talent, make use of an applicant tracking system that allows users to advertise jobs, gather resumes, and track applicants.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Important skills to teach your employees include:<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Client service.<\/li>\n<li>Communication and interpersonal skills.<\/li>\n<li>Time management.<\/li>\n<li>Handling of cleaning equipment, detergents, and other chemicals.<\/li>\n<li>Attention to detail and quality control skills.<\/li>\n<li>Health and safety rules.<\/li>\n<li>Compliance.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-cleaning-business#how-to-start-a-cleaning-business-section10-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-determine-your-ideal-candidate-288x288-20200729.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"11","name":"<p>Market your cleaning business.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Offer your services to friends and family.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>This is a great way to get started and to spread the message about your cleaning business. Encourage your family and friends to tell people about your cleaning business and what you've got to offer.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-cleaning-business#how-to-start-a-cleaning-business-section11-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-offer-services-to-family-and-friends-288x288-20200729.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Use free marketing options.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>There are free email and SMS marketing services available to help you cut your marketing expenses. You can also open a social media account for free on all popular platforms, including Facebook, LinkedIn, Twitter, and Instagram.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-cleaning-business#how-to-start-a-cleaning-business-section11-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-use-free-marketing-platforms-288x288-20200730.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Create a company website.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Your company website should be a great source of information, listing everything about your business's history and leadership, cleaning services, previous experience, rates, and contact information. Be sure to register your domain name so that potential clients can easily find your website.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-cleaning-business#how-to-start-a-cleaning-business-section11-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-company-website-288x288-20200729.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}}]}]}</script> <div
